{
    "ocr_text": "April 5, 1909.
Mr. W. G. Peth, Member, C.M.I. of A. No. 283,
The Naples Hotel,
Naples, N.Y.
Dear Sir and Brother:
In compliance with the request contained in your favor of the 3rd Inst., I am sending to you under separate cover a copy of the 'History of Trade Unions', which I think will contain the information you desire.
With best wishes, I am
Fraternally yours,
Sam[l?]ompersi
President,
American Federation of Labor.",
    "summary": "The letter, dated April 5, 1909, from the President of the American Federation of Labor to Mr. W. G. Peth, acknowledges a request from April 3 and mentions sending a copy of the 'History of Trade Unions' to provide the desired information.",
